The paper discusses models for embedding words in context, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of token embeddings for part-of-speech tagging and dependency parsing, which are common NLP tasks that fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of large amounts of unannotated text, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since it discusses the use of embeddings for representing semantic roles, which is a task that is related to image captioning and visual question answering.
